⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Earth, the Defended World
node TGL · TGL · ⟦Earth, the Defended World:TGL:89acf4⟧

WHO   — Earth, the Defended World — the homeworld
WHAT  — The stake of the entire mission of The Guardian Legend — the one world worth another world's destruction to save; the reason the Guardian goes into Naju at all.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Naju is falling toward Earth full of monsters, and a living world is worth defending; because some worlds are worth the price of another; because the Guardian was built and sent for this and nothing else.
HOW   — Not by acting, but by being — by being the world below, the thing defended, the destination of the long fall; by being worth the end of Naju.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the world worth saving — and one world will end so that I do not.

